						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 25 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold, for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple at Tiruppaḻaṉam a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> in Miṟai-kūṟṟam, by Nambaṉ Kaṇḍaṉ a servant of <hi rend="bold">Marudam-Baṭṭaṉ</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Śōḻavēḷār</hi> the headman of Karugāvūr in Āvūr-kūṟṟam. The gift was left in charge of three persons against the security of their land in the village.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
